div1.p: In the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Washington, Northern Division.
In re: Application of Ham Hung Wah for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. No. 1227.

On this 25th day of October, 1904, on application and notion of I. D. MoCutcheon, Esq., attorney for the petitioner herein, it is ordered that the aove entitled cause and and petition be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
IN THE Circuit COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON
In re- Ham Hung Wah vs. Habeas Corpus
